## Events tab (shell) — published events only

### How the feature works

- **Bottom nav label** is **Events** (route remains **`/feed`** for the shell branch). [FeedScreen](lib/screens/feed_screen.dart) header title **Events**.
- **Events (Expansion)** use Firestore **`events_mobile`** ([events_repository.dart](lib/services/events_repository.dart)) with the same field shape as curriculum events. **Published** = no `approval_status` or `approved`. Events tab and **Events** (`/events`) use `watchPublishedEvents()`. Admin-created events that target **both** curriculum and mobile share one **`event_id`** in **`events`** and **`events_mobile`** with `distribution: 'both'`; **Register** / **Unregister** updates **`events_mobile`** and, when `distribution == 'both'`, the matching **`events`** doc in the same transaction.
- **User-submitted events:** Members write only to **`events_mobile`** (`approval_status: 'pending'`). **Format** In person / Online, **required date and time**, optional flyer → Storage `events/member_uploads/{uid}/...`, then Firestore. The **date picker** only enables days from **four calendar days after today** onward (today plus the next three days, and all earlier dates, are not selectable). Submit still enforces **start at least 72 hours from now** (local date + time). **Digital Curriculum admin** merges **`events`** + **`events_mobile`** (`getAllEventsForAdmin`); **Where to publish** when creating: **Curriculum only**, **Expansion (mobile) only**, or **Both** (`createEvent` + `distribution`). Web public **`getEvents()`** reads **`events`** only. See `firestore.rules` for **`events`** (staff curriculum create) and **`events_mobile`** (member submit + staff mobile create).
- **Migration:** Older member submissions stored only under **`events`** do not appear in the app until copied into **`events_mobile`** (one-time data move if needed).
- **FAB:** Events tab → `/events/create` only (events); blocked with a snackbar when **`content_suspended`**. **Community posts** screen: top-level **`/posts`** with **`parentNavigatorKey: root`** (same pattern as **`/matching`**) so **`context.push('/posts')`** always resolves; [SocialFeedScreen](lib/screens/social_feed_screen.dart) stacks above the bottom nav. **+** FAB → `/feed/post/create`. Deep links: `/feed/post/create`, `/feed/post/:postId`. Post images upload to Storage **`feed_posts/member_uploads/{uid}/...`** (see `storage.rules`); Firestore field **`image_url`** on **`feed_posts/{postId}`**. **Likes** use subcollection **`feed_posts/{postId}/likes/{uid}`** ([feed_posts_repository.dart](lib/services/feed_posts_repository.dart)). [FeedPostCard](lib/widgets/feed_post_card.dart) shows **no** title/category chip or **share**; liked state uses **filled** heart in **`AppColors.primary`**; authors see **delete**; the like row sits **directly under** the post body (and non-compact timestamp) **without** a divider line above it. [CreatePostScreen](lib/screens/create_post_screen.dart): **description** first, **add image** below; publishes with **`post_category: General`**, empty **`post_title`** except image-only posts (**`Photo`**).
- **Event detail:** Unpublished events show a banner; **Register** is disabled until the event is published. **RSVPs:** [event_detail_screen.dart](lib/screens/event_detail_screen.dart) lists everyone in `registered_users` with photo/initials and display name from `users/{uid}`; **tap a row** (or chevron) opens **`showUserProfileModal`**; **Message** on each row (hidden for self) goes to `/messages/direct/{userId}` (same as the modal’s **Message** button).
- **Events list (`/events`) and Feed event cards:** Each card shows up to **five** RSVP rows ([EventRsvpAttendeeTile](lib/widgets/event_rsvp_attendee_tile.dart)); **View all N RSVPs** opens the event detail when there are more than five.
- **Profile modal:** Still opens from groups and anywhere `showUserProfileModal` is used. Shows **Tribe** (`tribe` fallback `industry`), optional **business logo** (`business_logo_url`), **Report** (writes **`user_reports`** for staff triage), and **Message** → `/messages/direct/{userId}`. **Posted jobs**, **Skill listings**, and **Events** use `where('author_id')` / `where('created_by')` **without** `orderBy` (sort client-side) so streams work without extra composite indexes; errors surface in the modal if rules or network fail.

## User reports & content suspension (staff)

### How the feature works

- **Firestore `user_reports`:** Members create docs (`reporter_id`, `reported_user_id`, `reason`, `status: open`, `created_at`). **Read/update/delete: staff** (`Admin` / `superAdmin` token claims), see root `firestore.rules`. **Profile modal → Report** uses a dedicated **`_ReportMemberDialog`** stateful widget so the **`TextEditingController` lives for the lifetime of the dialog** (`user_profile_modal.dart`); the dialog is shown with **`useRootNavigator: true`** to avoid route-stack issues under the bottom sheet. Older code held the controller outside the dialog and popped the route before dispose completed, which could trigger Flutter’s **`_dependents.isEmpty`** assertion and prevent the Firestore write from running reliably.
- **Staff UI — mobile:** **`/admin/reports`** ([admin_reports_screen.dart](lib/screens/admin_reports_screen.dart)); **Ban** and **Unsuspend** sit on each report card (no longer only under expand). **Profile & activity** expands a **readable** snapshot (profile fields, feed posts, mobile events, other reports) — not raw JSON. After **Ban** or **Unsuspend**, [UserReportsRepository.finalizeStaffModeration](lib/services/user_reports_repository.dart) runs **`moderateUserAccount`** then updates the report: **`status: resolved`**, **`staff_resolution`**: `ban` | `unsuspend`, **`resolved_at`**, **`resolved_by`**. Cards with a decision use muted styling and a **Final: …** badge; actions are hidden. The list still shows finalized reports (below open items) so you can see the outcome.
- **Staff UI — web:** **Digital Curriculum → Admin Panel → Expansion mobile** (and optional Next.js **Admin → Mobile & reports**) use the same **structured snapshot** UI, **Ban / Unsuspend** on cards, and the same Firestore fields after a decision. [UserReportsRepository](lib/services/user_reports_repository.dart) still exposes **Investigate** / **Resolve & lift** / **Dismiss** for other tooling; the mobile admin screens above do not surface those.
- **Client:** [UserReportsRepository](lib/services/user_reports_repository.dart), [AdminModerationRepository](lib/services/admin_moderation_repository.dart) (snapshot callable only), [content_action_guard.dart](lib/utils/content_action_guard.dart), and repositories call **`assertCallerNotContentSuspended()`** before creating posts, events, listings, groups, threads, comments, DMs, and replies.

## Mobile communities — admin placement & visibility (`groups_mobile`)

### How the feature works

- **`visibility`:** `public` (default) or `private`. **Public:** anyone signed in can **`joinGroup`** (subject to `Status` Open/Closed as before). **Private:** **`joinGroup`** rejects self-join; only staff-created membership (e.g. **`adminCreateMobileGroup`**) or future staff tooling can add UIDs to **`GroupMembers`**. [FsGroup](lib/models/group_thread_firestore.dart) exposes **`isPrivateCommunity`**; [groups_screen.dart](lib/screens/groups_screen.dart) shows a **Private** chip; [group_detail_screen.dart](lib/screens/group_detail_screen.dart) hides **Join** for private non-members and explains invite-only access.
- **Member-created groups:** [GroupThreadRepository.createGroup](lib/services/group_thread_repository.dart) sets **`visibility: public`**.
- **Staff-created groups:** Callable **`adminCreateMobileGroup`** (Next.js **Admin → Mobile & reports**): name, optional description/rules/category, **`visibility`**, **`Status`**, and **`placementRows`** `{ email, reportReason }[]`. Resolves each email with Admin Auth **`getUserByEmail`**, adds UIDs to **`GroupMembers`**, and stores audit rows in **`placement_audit`** (email, uid, reportReason, placedAt). Emails with no Auth user are returned as **`unresolvedEmails`** and skipped.
- **Cloud Functions:** `functions/src/callables/adminMobileModeration.ts` exports **`adminCreateMobileGroup`**, **`getUserModerationSnapshot`**, **`moderateUserAccount`**. **`joinGroup`** in [groupMembership.ts](../../functions/src/callables/groupMembership.ts) enforces private communities for `scope === "mobile"`.

## Home tab

### How the feature works

- Below **Welcome**, a **Latest job** / **Latest skill** row streams `expansion_jobs` and `expansion_skills` (newest first); tap opens Explore with **`/explore?filter=jobs`** or **`/explore?filter=skills`**; [ExploreScreen](lib/screens/explore_screen.dart) resolves the active filter from **`GoRouterState.of(context).uri`** so Home deep links show **Jobs** or **Skills** even under [StatefulShellRoute](lib/router/app_router.dart). Subtitles prefer **`skill_seeking`** / **`skill_offering`** when set, then industry and location. **Recent Activity** follows ([home_screen.dart](lib/screens/home_screen.dart) `_RecentActivityCard`): streams the latest **`feed_posts`** (**limit 2**) via [FeedPostsRepository.watchPosts](lib/services/feed_posts_repository.dart); each row is [FeedPostCard](lib/widgets/feed_post_card.dart) in **compact** mode with **`showImage: false`** (no inline photos on Home; open post for image), avatar + name → **`showUserProfileModal`**, **like** only. **View All** → **`/posts`**. **FAB +** on Home opens **`/feed/post/create`** ([create_post_screen.dart](lib/screens/create_post_screen.dart): description, optional photo below). **Your communities** (`groups_mobile`) lists snippets + `/groups/{groupId}`.

## Explore tab — jobs, skills, network search, DMs

### How the feature works

- **Jobs** and **skill listings** live in Firestore `expansion_jobs` and `expansion_skills` ([explore_listings_repository.dart](lib/services/explore_listings_repository.dart)). Fields include **`skill_seeking`** (job — array of 1–30 labels from the curriculum list in [curriculum_onboarding_data.dart](lib/data/curriculum_onboarding_data.dart)), **`skill_offering`** (skill listing — same), **`industry`** (dropdown from [explore_posting_industries.dart](lib/data/explore_posting_industries.dart), includes **Technology**), **`location_mode`** (`remote` \| `in_person`), and **`location`** (stored as `Remote` or city/state text; **In person** prefills from `users/{uid}` **`city`** + **`state`** via `UserProfileRepository.getCityStateLineForUser`). Legacy docs may store a single string for `skill_seeking` / `skill_offering`; the app maps that to a one-element list. Explore cards and home **Latest job/skill** rows join selected skills with ` · `. Explore shows filters **All / Jobs / Skills / Network Search**. **`/explore?filter=jobs`**, **`skills`**, or **`network`** pre-selects the chip; [ExploreScreen](lib/screens/explore_screen.dart) reads **`GoRouterState.of(context).uri.queryParameters['filter']`**, and chip taps call **`context.go('/explore')`** or **`context.go('/explore?filter=…')`** so the URL stays the source of truth ([app_router.dart](lib/router/app_router.dart) shell route **`/explore`**). **Network Search** ([explore_screen.dart](lib/screens/explore_screen.dart)): search field (min 2 characters, debounced); [UserProfileRepository.searchMembersByName](lib/services/user_profile_repository.dart) loads candidates via Firestore **`orderBy` + range** on **`first_name`** and **`last_name`** (plus title-case prefix), then **case-insensitive** token matching on `first_name` / `last_name` (and legacy **`firstName`** / **`lastName`**). Results show avatar, profession, location; **tap** opens **`showUserProfileModal`**; **Message** goes to `/messages/direct/{uid}`. The signed-in user is excluded from hits.
- **Post flows:** FAB **+** → bottom sheet: **Post a job** (`/explore/jobs/create` — onboarding-style **Skills seeking** multiselect via [ExploreCurriculumSkillsMultiselect](lib/widgets/explore_curriculum_skills_multiselect.dart) + title, industry, location mode, optional company/description), **Offer a skill** (`/explore/skills/create` — **Skills offering** multiselect + headline, industry, location, summary). No separate **Skills hub** entry from Explore (full list still at `/explore/skills` if linked elsewhere).
- **Dev seed (fixed fixtures):** `infra/scripts/seed-expansion-stage-mock.js` (npm `seed:dev:expansion-mock` / `seed:stage:expansion-mock`) seeds **only** **20 Auth users** with fixed UIDs **`user_001` … `user_020`**, matching **`users/{uid}`** docs (emails like **`alana.pierce@example.com`**, **`roles: ["Alumni"]`**, bio/profession/skills/goals from **`MOCK_USERS`**), and **20** **`feed_posts`** docs (**`seed_mock_feed_00` … `19`**) whose visible body is **`post_details`** (**`post_title`** empty, **`post_category`:** `General`); post **author** **i** is **`MOCK_USERS[i]`** (1:1). It does **not** write `expansion_jobs`, `expansion_skills`, `events_mobile`, or `groups_mobile`. **Auth for the script (required for real runs):** a **service account JSON** via **`--credentials`** or **`GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS`** — the script exits with instructions if neither is set (default application credentials are not assumed). Run from **monorepo root** (`WorkingMortarProj`), not `expansion_network/`. PowerShell: **`$env:GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS = "C:\\path\\to\\mortar-stage-adminsdk.json"`** then **`npm.cmd run seed:stage:expansion-mock`** if **`npm.ps1` is blocked by execution policy**; otherwise **`npm run seed:stage:expansion-mock`**. Or **`node infra/scripts/seed-expansion-stage-mock.js --project mortar-stage --credentials "C:\\path\\to\\file.json"`**. Password for newly created accounts defaults from **`SEED_USER_PASSWORD`** or **`MortarDevSeed!2026`**. Edit **`MOCK_USERS`** / **`MOCK_FEED_POSTS`** in that file to change data.
- **Profile avatars on listings:** [PosterProfileAvatar](lib/widgets/poster_profile_avatar.dart) on job/skill cards and in **Direct chat** (header + message rows); **Messages** list avatars open the peer’s profile modal.
- **Messaging about a listing:** **Message** on a job or skill card opens `/messages/direct/{authorId}?attach=job&id={jobId}` or `attach=skill&id={skillId}`. [DirectChatScreen](lib/screens/direct_chat_screen.dart) shows a pending attachment strip; the first send includes `attachment_type` / `attachment_id` on the message doc. [MessagingAttachmentPreview](lib/widgets/messaging_attachment_preview.dart) renders the card above the text in the thread.
- **Direct messages:** `dm_threads/{uidSmall_uidLarge}` with `participant_ids` (sorted), `updated_at`, `last_preview`, `last_sender_id`. Messages in `dm_threads/{id}/messages/{msgId}` with `sender_id`, `text`, `created_at`, optional attachment fields. [MessagesScreen](lib/screens/messages_screen.dart) lists threads for the current user (`array-contains` + `orderBy updated_at` — composite index in `firestore.indexes.json`).
- **Expansion user matching (Cloud Function + app):** Callable **`runExpansionUserMatching`** ([runExpansionUserMatching.ts](../../functions/src/callables/runExpansionUserMatching.ts)) writes **`users/{uid}/expansion_matches/{matchedUserId}`** (owner read-only in `firestore.rules`). Payload includes **`score`** (0–100 weighted: ~70% skills / ~20% goals / ~10% context), **`rawTotal`**, **`skillScore`**, **`goalScore`**, **`contextScore`**, **`mutualSkillBonus`**, **`aNeedsFromB`**, **`bNeedsFromA`**, **`goalMatches`**, **`sameCity`**, **`sameIndustry`**, **`algorithmVersion`**. **Eligibility:** `networkAccess == true`, curriculum onboarding **or** Expansion onboarding complete, and at least one of **`confident_skills`** / **`desired_skills`**. **Excludes:** self; anyone already in a **`dm_threads`** doc with the user; UIDs listed on **`users/{uid}.expansion_dismissed_match_uids`** (optional string array the client may maintain). **`scope`:** `"self"` (default, any signed-in user) or `"all"` (Admin / **superAdmin** only, recomputes everyone). **Top N:** 10; **min raw score** 15. Deploy with **`firebase deploy --only functions,firestore:rules`**. **Gen 2 / Cloud Run:** registered with **`invoker: "public"`** so the HTTPS endpoint accepts app traffic; Firebase still validates the caller’s ID token (`request.auth`) — same pattern as **`initializeUserSession`** in `expansionInvite.ts` (without this, Android can surface **`[unauthenticated] UNAUTHENTICATED`** before the handler runs). **Mobile UI (`/matching`, [matching_screen.dart](lib/screens/matching_screen.dart)):** **Start matching** calls the callable with **`scope: self`** via [ExpansionMatchingRepository](lib/services/expansion_matching_repository.dart); a **non-dismissible loading dialog** shows until the callable returns. The screen **streams** `expansion_matches` ordered by **`score`** descending. Each **card** shows profile preview (**`UserProfileRepository.getUserDoc`** — name, photo, profession, industry, city/state), **Why you matched** (goal lines, skill exchange summaries, optional same city/industry / mutual bonus), **match %**, **Message** → `/messages/direct/{matchedUserId}`, and **tap anywhere on the card** (except the button) opens **`showUserProfileModal`**. If the callable writes zero rows, a **SnackBar** hints to refresh the profile.

